This paper focuses on causal inference and visual reasoning using deep neural networks, which are topics commonly studied in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also introduces pixel-wise masking and adversarial perturbation, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and computer security (cs.CR) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the use of causal effects for detecting adversarial examples, which is a topic commonly studied in natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer security (cs.CR) sub-categories.
